<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="149" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,820,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,964,991]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[329,452,965,991]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[329,452,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">P. oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mostly resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[662,744,965,991]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis box="[662,744,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">P. latus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the size of the eyes and coloration but differs by the shape of sclerites of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,820,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1036,1063]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[515,622,1036,1063]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="3.35">3.35 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head dark brown with clypeus yellowish; pronotum light brown to yellowish; elytra dark brown, nearly black in anterior half, more yellowish in posterior half; abdomen dark brown to nearly black with posterior margin of segments yellowish; legs and antennae yellow. Head 
<quantity box="[1273,1373,1109,1135]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[151,250,1145,1171]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
wide; eyes large and prominent; 0.33 times as long as total length of head; 0.87 times as long as postocular length; sides approximately parallel; posterior margin straight; slightly depressed on central vertex in front of neck. Pronotum 
<quantity box="[269,369,1217,1243]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[441,541,1217,1243]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
wide; widest close to anterior angles; anterior margin slightly curved; posterior margin less curved than anterior margin; sides converging posteriad Elytra 
<quantity box="[1019,1121,1252,1279]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1197,1299,1252,1279]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
wide; sides slightly convexly curved; widest in the middle; humeral angles rounded and obtuse, but conspicuously developed; hind wings developed; posterior angles nearly rectangular; posterior margin triangularly emarginate; suture 0.82 times as long as lateral side; microtuberculate punctation larger than on head and pronotum; with yellow pubescence pointing posteriad; posterior edge with fringe of short dark setae; surface matt. Abdomen with dense punctation; long pubescence pointing posteriad. Aedeagus elongate; 
<quantity box="[790,891,1432,1459]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
long; approximately four times as long as wide; subparallel; slightly convergent to apex; sclerites with broad base and apical hook; short, 
<quantity box="[1152,1251,1469,1495]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1407,1468,1495]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1895,1920]" captionTargetBox="[232,1346,220,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[164,1424,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Aedeagus of Pseudastenus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively, figures 51–54 including microscopic detail of basal slerites. 48. P. ribeirocostae sp. nov.; 49. P. ferrugineus sp. nov.; 50. P. latus sp. nov.; 51. P. barretoi; 52. P. oculatus sp. nov.; 53. P. amazonicus sp. nov.; 54. P. schubarti sp. nov. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3724309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3724309/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,820,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1505,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name derives from the Latin word “oculatus” meaning concerning eyes, and refers to the large eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,820,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1576,1603]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Geographical records.</emphasis>
The specimens are collected from different places of the Várzea of the Rio Solimões, Amazonas (
<collectingCountry box="[284,358,1613,1640]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Brazil</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,820,1675]" box="[199,1112,1648,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,394,1648,1675]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Biological notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[401,523,1649,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[401,523,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">P. oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from the litter layer of Várzea forests.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
